id: pm-fmjy
title: "CodeFactor/Duplication: remove duplicated code blocks (×20: 2 Critical, 3 Major, 15 Minor)"
description: "CodeFactor's duplicate-code detector found **20 clones**.\n\n## Breakdown + lists\n\n- Critical ×2 — https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Duplication&groupId=2\n- Major ×3 — https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Duplication&groupId=1\n- Minor ×15 — https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Duplication&groupId=4\n\n## Strategy\n\n- Production code: extract the duplicated block into a shared helper/constant/module. (This repo already favors shared dedup helpers — see prior chore pm-1b96.)\n- Test code: a large share of duplication lives in the command spec files (`create-command.spec.ts`, `update-command.spec.ts`); factor common arrange/act setup into shared test helpers or fixtures and parametrize repeated cases.\n- Tackle Critical + Major first.\n\n## Constraints\n\nBehavior-preserving. New shared helpers must themselves be covered to keep the 100% coverage gate green. Mind the 120-file/dir static cap if adding helper files."
type: Task
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[4]: code-quality,codefactor,duplication,refactor
created_at: "2026-06-26T13:33:10.951Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-26T20:02:53.444Z"
assignee: codex
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: "First milestone: the 2 Critical + 3 Major duplication clones are removed by extracting shared helpers/fixtures. Stretch: Minor clones to 0. Extracted helpers are covered; full coverage suite green at 100%; pnpm typecheck + quality gates pass."
parent: pm-92if
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-26T19:05:47.033Z",codex-codefactor-sdk-cli-20260626,"Evidence: removed CodeFactor-reported shipped duplication by single-sourcing create/update --unset field metadata, create/update command option key lists, and SDK update-many/close-many filter contracts; generated package runtime loaders and plugin MCP launchers are now explicitly excluded from CodeFactor because generator check tests enforce drift. Passed: pnpm build; targeted create/update/runtime-loader/generator/plugin/package tests (7 files, 254 tests); pnpm contracts:check; pnpm quality:static; pnpm typecheck; pnpm security:scan; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (256 files, 5133 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines)."
  "2026-06-26T19:43:37.160Z",codex,"Investigation note: CodeFactor docs for ignored files say folder/global file patterns are configured in repository Settings > Ignore Files, while files containing an auto-generated marker are ignored automatically. The hosted CodeFactor issue views still show paths covered by .codefactor.yml, so this branch adds explicit auto-generated markers to generated package runtime loaders and plugin MCP wrappers, with generator drift checks proving they are not hand-edited."
  "2026-06-26T20:02:53.444Z",codex,"Evidence: CodeFactor duplication remediation now covers generated runtime loaders/wrappers with explicit auto-generated markers, SDK list/search filter contract tables with shared constants, list/search compact filter echo with applyCommonItemFilterEcho, create/update runtime unset matching via shared-unset-fields, and config canonical key typing from core/config/positional-value. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (256 files, 5133 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines), pnpm typecheck, pnpm quality:static, pnpm contracts:check, node scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.mjs --check, node scripts/gen-plugin-mcp-wrappers.mjs --check, git diff --check, and isolated temp PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH lifecycle smoke item temp-codefactor-4vxe with healthOk=true validateOk=true validateWarnings=0. Strict diagnostic node scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs --max-complexity 100 --json now reports duplicate_chunks=[]; remaining findings are complexity-only and stay on pm-arzz."
